    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "I will spend a couple days and end up with eight honking PRs of world changing features that would have taken us three weeks previously" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_ScarletBackPressureQuote> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "every single response prompts another action, right? And while that's good for token consumption, it's not good for humans because if the prompt is, do you want me to do that?" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_TonyAITrapQuote> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "Each one of these is somebody telling us really valuable information about why them understanding the product value does not equal a sale." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_ScarletPurchaseTriggerQuote> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "People like me have 10 repos on the go with Claude right now and... all this tooling and different skills... I'm worried what's going to break or cross over." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_TechnicalChaosQuote> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "Everything you said about committing and pulling and all of that is completely foreign to me." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_OutsideTechBetaUserGitHubOpacityFeedback> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "Text message, in certain contexts, is absolutely the right move. But in a lot of skeptical or lower-trust contexts, texting is so associated with spam now that requiring someone to text might actually be a real downside." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_OutsideTechBetaUserSMSSpamCodedQuote> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "I'm a key candidate for this because I forget as much as I remember." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_CustomerEngManagerForgetQuote1> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "We gave you pros and cons and you were to go away and figure out which one suits and come back with a proposal. We didn't give you a full solution, we just gave you options." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_OptionsVsDecisionsQuote> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "The 'felt vs. shown' crux is challenged: Jul 2026 evidence argues value is fully showable without the prospect's own data — inverting the prior hedge that prospects must try it themselves before value lands." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_ShowVsDemoProof> ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_ScarletFeltVsShownQuote> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "Activation gap may already be closed: the deployment layer providing a concrete demonstrable application was confirmed as sufficient by a design collaborator, qualifying the 'investment vs. tool' framing as a past-state problem." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_ActivationGapClosed> ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_ActivationGap> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "Staffing AI adoption wall introduces an organizational-conflict vector distinct from all other adoption friction: the blocker is internal politics triggered by AI working too well, not product legibility or onboarding." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_StaffingAIAdoptionWall> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "Scarlet's uncertainty about pushing non-enterprise archetypes (Apr 2026) sits in tension with the non-technical onboarding friction cluster, which assumes those archetypes remain in scope." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_ScarletUnsureArchetypes> ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_OutsideTechBetaUserGitHubOpacityFeedback> ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_OutsideTechBetaUserToolLanguageFeedback> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "Ambient adoption framing positions the tool as needing to be invisible/zero-extra-work, which sits in tension with the onboarding friction cluster that requires active user steps (install, commit, compile)." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_AmbientAdoption> ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_OutsideTechBetaUserToolLanguageFeedback> ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_IdentityOnboardingGap> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "Bottleneck framing extends beyond individuals to processes (Scarlet, Jul 2026), potentially broadening the target beyond the 'forgetting person at the decision junction' diagnosis." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_BottleneckProcessesQuote> ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_ForgettingBottleneckIsRole> ] ;
    narr:writer "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.6" .
